   *(The technique section that unlocks the "how does that actually work" question. Blooming gel explained in reader-friendly terms: a delay-polymerisation clear coat that lets pigment diffuse outward like watercolour petals before curing. Why it's gone viral [millions of TikTok views]. The resulting effect: soft, diffused, almost botanical-illustration quality. Who it's for: the person who wants floral art without the precision of hand-painting. Salon vs DIY feasibility. Summer colourways: tropical ombre, hibiscus blur, micro roses in peach and coral.)*

