   *(The statement tier. Builder gel or acrylic sculpted petal by petal — roses, peonies, ranunculus — typically as a single accent bloom on the ring finger. What it looks like vs photographs. Honest salon guidance: 90–120 minutes, £80–£120 / $80–$120, salon-only — the most requested 3D styles for summer 2026. The summer shift: tropical 3D blooms (hibiscus, plumeria) alongside the spring roses. Durability note: raised elements require care. Link to spring-floral-nails cross-site for the full technique deep-dive. Occasions: events, weddings, vacations.)*

6. **Pressed Flower Nails: The Most Romantic Style in the Category**
   *(Real dried botanicals encapsulated under hard gel — the design that looks like an illustration but is actually three-dimensional. What makes pressed flower nails distinctive: the translucency, the uniqueness of each set, the artisanal quality. Durability: 2–3 weeks with proper hard gel encapsulation. Care note: botanicals must be fully dried before application. Salon-only. Who it's for: the romantic, the maximalist-with-restraint, the bride-adjacent. Summer specific: tropical micro-flowers, wildflower meadow sets, single pressed bloom on a sheer nude.)*

7. **Tropical Floral Nails: The Out-of-Office Manicure**
   *(The summer-specific floral sub-category. Hibiscus accents, plumeria blooms, tropical florals on gradient or ombre bases — NailTok's "out-of-office" signal. What makes tropical florals distinct from garden florals: saturated colour, larger scale, vacation energy. Blooming gel hibiscus is the accessible version; hand-painted or 3D hibiscus is the salon statement. Skin tone note: tropical saturated shades look particularly strong on medium and deep tones. Link to beach-nails cross-site here. Occasions: holidays, festivals, vacation, beach events.)*

8. **Which Floral Nail Style Is Actually Yours? A Quick Guide**
   *(The decision tool — the section every competitor is missing. Map personality/aesthetic to style type:*
